<br>
Why would anyone possibly set their /roleplay tag on if they have absolutely no intention to role play in any sense of the word? If other people not knowing your level means that much to you, just go /anon. So people can't see your guild tag, bfd. You obviously only want people to know the bare minimum about you anyway, what is the problem? <br>
<br>
Personally if I encounter someone with a purple tag, it is a debate as to whether to runway to avoid complications, hide/sneak to avoid complications, or approach them and hope that I am not about to recieve a scathing response because of what race I was born. If I bother to do any of these and you tell me &quot;Sup?&quot; then I am at a loss for words...not the response I was expecting at all.<br>
