<br>
. turns your name purple == I want to roleplay<br>
. hides your race == I don't want you to know what languages I speak<br>
. hides your level == I don't want to tell you my level<br>
. hides your class == I don't want to tell you my class<br>
. hides your zone == I don't want to tell you where I am<br>
<br>
People could be using it for any one of those effects.  Notice that there are 5 effects and only one of them indicates a desire to RP.  It looks to me like Verant/SOE screwed up again.  They should have made 5 individual controls.  Instead they made one giant one and lumped them all together.  Failing to recognize the issue and buying into the dumb /roleplay name for that particular in game feature when 80% of the feature is unrelated to roleplay says more about the person complaining that it does about anyone that uses that feature. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gothmatum>Gothmatum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/18/03 7:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3885.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.zoominternet.net/~gothmatum/images/eqpagoth.gif width=93 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Actually, the problem is ..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>80% of the feature is unrelated to roleplay<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
