<br>
That being said, I am almost never in /roleplay.  I put it on when I don't want to be found - it's like hanging a do-not-disturb tag on my door.  Otherwise, I don't mind letting people know my class, season, and location - it saves a lot of stupid questions.  Location especially, since it demonstrates to the observant folk whether I'm languishing in PoK and can be approached for buffs and rezzes, or whether I'm embattled in a fighting zone. <br>
<br>
And I don't think I've ever gone /anon, because I see that as a way to take off guild tags so you can do a sneaky or OOC thing that a good representative of your guild wouldn't want to be caught doing - lol. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.chivalrousvalor.com/sigs/goodelf.JPG" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
